The paper deals with the analysis of bit-error rate (BER) for one-dimensional constellations, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and communication (cs.COMM). The analysis involves the use of labeling and patterns, which are concepts related to data structures (cs.DS) and signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the analysis of the number of patterns for different BER values involves the use of algorithms and network protocols, which are topics related to computer networks (cs.NI).
